OL,3,CShared parental leave proposed to
OL,4,Cmodernise 'outdated' childcare rights
OL,6,F"The shift from maternity leave to
OL,7,Fshared parental leave in most
OL,8,Fdeveloped nations was driven by a
OL,9,Fdesire to promote gender equality,
OL,10,Fsupport diverse family structures, and
OL,11,Fenable more flexible caregiving
OL,12,Farrangements.
OL,14,F"It reflects a broader commitment to
OL,15,Fmodernising workplace policies and
OL,16,Fempowering both parents to participate
OL,17,Fin early childcare."
